-- French Stocks: Alstom, ArcelorMittal, Zodiac Shares Lead Gains in Paris
-- David Altaner
-- 2010-07-06T15:41:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/french-stocks-alstom-arcelormittal-zodiac-shares-lead-gains-in-paris.html

          
          
             The benchmark CAC 40 Index increased
90.9, or 2.7 percent, to 3,423.36, the biggest gain since May
27. The SBF 120 Index climbed 2.6 percent.  
 The following were among the most active stocks traded in
France today.  
 Alstom SA  (ALO FP) gained 4.5 percent to 38.41 euros, the
biggest gain in three weeks. Alstom and partner Societe
Nationale des Chemins de Fer Francais are in a good position to
win a Saudi Arabian contract for a high-speed rail link between
Medina and Mecca, Les Echos said, without citing anyone.  
 ArcelorMittal  (MT NA) rose 5.8 percent to 22.58 euros.
Hunan Valin Steel Co. said a Chinese commission approved plans
to form a venture with a unit of the world’s biggest steelmaker
to produce automobile sheets, according to a statement on the
website of Shenzhen’s stock exchange.  
 Renault SA  (RNO FP) increased 3.7 percent to 31.13 euros.
India’s Bajaj Auto Ltd. said it will supply low-cost autos to
the French automaker for local sales after the companies dropped
plans for a manufacturing joint venture.  
 Zodiac Aerospace  (ZC FP) rallied 7.4 percent to 39.60
euros, the biggest gain since January, 2009. Europe’s biggest
maker of airplane seats was upgraded to “buy” from “hold” at
Societe Generale SA.  
